chain.task:
Implement or build according to this plan. Run the relevant build/test command when possible and report commands, exit codes, and important output.

Plan:
{outputs.plan}

Review the build result and current diff for correctness, regressions, missing validation, and risky changes. Return concrete findings only.

Build result:
{outputs.buildResult}

Analyze the build and review results. You must finish by calling structured_output with exactly this shape: { status: 'pass' | 'fail', issues: [...] }. Use issues: [] when everything is clean. Each issue should include title, details, severity, source, and suggestedCheck. Do not finish with prose, markdown, or code fences. If the structured_output call is rejected because the payload does not match the schema, correct the payload and call structured_output again. Retry up to a maximum of 5 structured_output attempts before reporting that you are blocked.

Build result:
{outputs.buildResult}

Review result:
{outputs.reviewResult}

parallel.task:
Do root-cause analysis for this issue. Do not modify project/source files. Return: likely cause, impacted files/areas, smallest safe fix, and validation command.

Issue title: {issue.title}
Severity: {issue.severity}
Source: {issue.source}
Details: {issue.details}
Suggested check: {issue.suggestedCheck}

chain.task:
If issueReport.status is pass and there are no issues, do nothing and return NOOP. Otherwise, fix the reported issues using the RCA reports. Use a bounded repair loop of at most 3 attempts: RCA -> fix -> focused check. Do not expand scope beyond the reported issues. Report changed files, commands run, validation output, and unresolved issues.

Issue report:
{outputs.issueReport}

RCA reports:
{outputs.rcaReports}

Run final validation after fixes: build/test and any suggested checks. You must finish by calling structured_output with status pass only if the build/review is clean. Do not finish with prose, markdown, or code fences. If the structured_output call is rejected because the payload does not match the schema, correct the payload and call structured_output again. Retry up to a maximum of 5 structured_output attempts before reporting that you are blocked.

Initial issue report:
{outputs.issueReport}

Fix result:
{outputs.fixResult}

If validationReport.status is pass and remainingIssues is empty, commit and push the completed work. If validation failed, do not commit or push; report remaining issues and recommended next steps.

